subSubSection.paragraph:
e occipital (
Fig. 3 F
) is nearly vertical in its lower and middle parts, and tilted slightly backwards and upwards in its superior part. e depression in the centre of the major occipital crest is clearly visible from this angle. In ventral view (
Figs 3A
; 
4A
), the basioccipital muscular tubercule is strong. For the skull MIL 162 the posterior part of the post-palatal notch is posterior to M2/ and it is more advanced (interval M1/-M2/) in the only Vialette skull where such an observation is possible.

